  "prompt": "I have a very old account in central bank in which no mobile number is registered. How to register my mobile number now?",
  "response": "To register your mobile number with your old account at the central bank, you will typically need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the Branch**: Go to the nearest branch of the central bank where you hold your account.\n\n2. **Identity Verification**: Make sure to bring a valid ID, such as a passport, driver's license, or national ID card, for identity verification purposes.\n\n3. **Fill Out the Form**: Ask for the relevant form required to update or register your mobile number in your account. This form could be a 'Customer Information Update' form or something similar.\n\n4. **Submit Required Documents**: You may need to provide additional documents like proof of address or your old account details.\n\n5. **Authorization**: Sign the form and provide any additional information required by the bank for verification.\n\n6. **Verification Process**: The bank will process your request and may take some time to verify your credentials. They might contact you for any further information or clarification during this period.\n\n7. **Confirmation**: Once your mobile number is registered, you should receive a confirmation either via email, SMS, or postal mail, depending on the bank's communication policies.\n\nRemember, processes might vary slightly depending on the country and specific banking institution. Always check the bank's official website or contact their customer service for the most accurate and detailed instructions.",
